14/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Parliament will start debating a series of laws related to the decentralisation process in the next couple of months, Parliament Speaker Nikola Popovski said Monday (13 October). The measures would have to take effect by the summer of next year to be implemented in the next local elections, scheduled to take place in October 2004.
In other news, Macedonia's main opposition party, VMRO-DPMNE, pledged Monday to fully support the upcoming campaign to collect illegal weapons. The six-week project is to begin on 1 November. (Dnevnik - 14/10/03; MIA, A1 TV - 13/10/03)
